cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.GR

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Networks and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with topology control problem for wireless ad hoc networks.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a new algorithm for computing a spanner of bounded degree.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with graph structures and spanners.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the paper deals with unit disk graphs and their geometric properties.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with geometric structures and their visualization.
